Foot and Mouth Disease in Uruguay
Follow-up report No. 9
Translation of information received on 21 June 2001 from Dr Carlos A.
Correa Messuti, Ministry of Animal Production, Agriculture and
Fisheries, Montevideo:
End of previous report period: 13 June 2001 (see Disease Information,
14 [24, 145, dated 15 June 2001).
End of this report period: 21 June 2001.
* The technical criterion used to determine that an outbreak is
extinguished is a minimum period of 30 days since the last sick animal.
Total number of animals in the outbreaks detected from 14 to 20 June
2001:
species: bovine / ovine / sui
susceptible: 63 643 / 38 309 / 61
cases: 2438 / -- / --
deaths: ­- / -- / --
destroyed: -- / -- / --
slaughtered: -- / -- / --
Control measures during reporting period:
- Strict measures for the control of outbreaks, disinfection and
confinement are being maintained. - Since 7 June 2001, vaccinated
susceptible animals may legally leave foot and mouth disease-free
zones.
- The second emergency mass vaccination of dairy cattle has been in
progress since 16 June 2001; as of 21 June, 80% of the dairy cattle
population has already received this booster injection.
